The HorseyHerd AUP License requires that anyone using the source code has their source code open-source on GitHub. As long as the source code of the project is open-source on GitHub, the source-code may also be provided anywhere else.
The HorseyHerd AUP License requires updates from the original software to be used in some aspect of the project until discontinued.
The HorseyHerd AUP License means that upon the software being discontinued, HorseyHerd (and all groups below, such as HorseyHerd Studios) now are the owners of that software. But until the software is discontinued, the individual using the source-code of the software owns their code, and owes 0 royalties, payments, etc.
